TITLE: Calling Python Template Function from External Module in syslog-ng
DESCRIPTION: Configures syslog-ng to use a Python function (`template_function`) defined in an external module (`mytemplate`). It calls this function from within a file destination's template using the dotted notation `$(python mytemplate.template_function)`. Syslog-ng automatically imports the `mytemplate` module when encountering this syntax.
SOURCE: https://github.com/syslog-ng/syslog-ng/blob/develop/modules/python-modules/README.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: syslog-ng-config
CODE:
```
@version: 4.0

log {
    source { tcp(port(2000)); };
    destination { file("logfile" template("$ISODATE $(python mytemplate.template_function)")); };
};
```

