TITLE: Configuring Templated Header Values for Loki Destination - Config
DESCRIPTION: This configuration illustrates setting a header with a template in the loki() destination of syslog-ng. syslog-ng must support Loki destination and value templating in header arguments. The header() parameter can interpolate values, here using a macro for per-message attributes. Input is structured log messages; output is log events sent to Loki with custom headers generated from the template. Any macros or variables referenced must be available in the context of message processing.
SOURCE: https://github.com/syslog-ng/syslog-ng/blob/develop/news/feature-5184.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: config
CODE:
```
destination d_loki {
    loki(
        url("https://loki.example:3100/loki/api/v1/push")
        header("X-Trace-Id", "${trace_id}")
    );
};
```

