TITLE: Configuring syslog-ng to Forward Apache Logs to Remote Host - syslog-ng
DESCRIPTION: This syslog-ng configuration receives logs from an Apache server (by reading /var/log/apache2/access.log) and forwards them to a remote syslog server on IP 1.2.3.4, TCP port 514. The configuration defines a file source, a TCP destination, and sets up a log path connecting the two. Place this configuration in syslog-ng.conf for use with the relevant Docker container.
SOURCE: https://github.com/syslog-ng/syslog-ng/blob/develop/docker/README.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: syslog-ng
CODE:
```
source s_apache {
  file("/var/log/apache2/access.log");
};

destination d_remote {
  tcp("1.2.3.4" port(514));
};

log {
  source(s_apache);
  destination(d_remote);
};
```

