TITLE: Configuring TLS Authentication for BigQuery Destination in syslog-ng
DESCRIPTION: This configuration snippet demonstrates how to use the `auth()` option within the `bigquery()` destination driver in `syslog-ng` to specify Transport Layer Security (TLS) authentication. It requires providing paths to the Certificate Authority file (`ca-file`), the client's private key file (`key-file`), and the client's certificate file (`cert-file`) to establish a secure connection to Google BigQuery.
SOURCE: https://github.com/syslog-ng/syslog-ng/blob/develop/news/feature-5174-2.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: config
CODE:
```
``` config
bigquery (
    ...
    auth(
        tls(
            ca-file("/path/to/ca.pem")
            key-file("/path/to/key.pem")
            cert-file("/path/to/cert.pem")
        )
    )
);
```
```

