TITLE: Configuring Keep-Alive Options for opentelemetry() in syslog-ng
DESCRIPTION: This configuration snippet demonstrates setting keep-alive parameters for the `opentelemetry()` destination (and similarly for `syslog-ng-otlp()`). The `keep-alive()` block contains `time()` (keep-alive packet interval in milliseconds), `timeout()` (timeout for keep-alive pings in milliseconds), and `max-pings-without-data()` (maximum keep-alive pings without data before closing the connection, 0 means infinite).
SOURCE: https://github.com/syslog-ng/syslog-ng/blob/develop/news/feature-5174-1.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: config
CODE:
```
``` config
opentelemetry(
    ...
    keep-alive(time(20000) timeout(10000) max-pings-without-data(0))
);
```
```

