TITLE: Enabling Program Name Validation in a syslog-ng Network Source
DESCRIPTION: This configuration snippet shows how to enable program name validation (`check-program`) alongside hostname validation (`check-hostname`) for a network source in syslog-ng. When enabled, program names within incoming RFC3164 messages will be checked against specific character rules and the requirement of containing at least one alphabetical character.
SOURCE: https://github.com/syslog-ng/syslog-ng/blob/develop/news/feature-5264.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: plaintext
CODE:
```
source { network(flags(check-hostname, check-program)); };
```

