TITLE: Embedding Python Template Function in syslog-ng Configuration
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates embedding a Python function (`template_function`) directly within a syslog-ng configuration using the top-level `python {}` block. This function accepts a `LogMessage` object (`msg`), concatenates message header and content, and returns a byte string. It's subsequently invoked within a file destination's template using `$(python template_function)`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/syslog-ng/syslog-ng/blob/develop/modules/python-modules/README.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: syslog-ng-config
CODE:
```
@version: 4.0

python {

def template_function(msg):
    return b"Hello World from Python! Original message: " + msg['MSGHDR'] + msg['MESSAGE']


};

log {
    source { tcp(port(2000)); };
    destination { file("logfile" template("$ISODATE $(python template_function)")); };
};
```

