TITLE: Explicitly Reloading Python Module on syslog-ng Reload
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates using the `importlib.reload()` function within a `python {}` block to force a reload of an imported Python module (`mymodule`) every time the syslog-ng configuration is reloaded (e.g., via `syslog-ng-ctl reload`). This ensures changes within the module are applied without a full syslog-ng restart and resets the module's state.
SOURCE: https://github.com/syslog-ng/syslog-ng/blob/develop/modules/python-modules/README.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
python {

import mymodule
import importlib

# reload mymodule every time syslog-ng reloads
importlib.reload(mymodule)

};
```

