TITLE: Defining Basic Python Destination Driver Class for syslog-ng
DESCRIPTION: Provides the basic structure for a custom Python destination driver in a file (e.g., `mydestination.py`). It defines a class `MyDestination` inheriting from `syslogng.LogDestination`. The essential `send` method must be implemented; it receives a `LogMessage` object (`msg`) and should contain the logic to forward the message, returning `True` on success or `False` on failure.
SOURCE: https://github.com/syslog-ng/syslog-ng/blob/develop/modules/python-modules/README.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
from syslogng import LogDestination

class MyDestination(LogDestination):
    def send(self, msg):
	return True

```

