TITLE: Configuring syslog-ng with TCP Source and Elasticsearch Destination
DESCRIPTION: This syslog-ng configuration example sets up multiple sources (`s_local` using `internal()` and `s_network` using `tcp`) and an Elasticsearch destination (`d_elastic`). It configures the `elasticsearch2` driver with parameters like library directory, index/type naming patterns, time zone, client mode, and cluster URLs. A log statement directs messages from the network source to the Elasticsearch destination.
SOURCE: https://github.com/syslog-ng/syslog-ng/blob/develop/modules/java/README.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: syslog-ng
CODE:
```
@version: 3.28

options {
  threaded(yes);
};

source s_local {
        internal();
};

