TITLE: Configuring Multiple Wildcard File Sources and Destinations in syslog-ng (config)
DESCRIPTION: This configuration snippet sets up two separate file sources using wildcards to monitor files matching /path/*.log, each with a distinct persist-name. Both sources are routed to a stdout() destination using separate log blocks. This setup is used to demonstrate and verify fixes for crashes that occur when the same wildcard pattern is used in multiple log sources. The sample requires syslog-ng configuration context with version and includes, and the use of persist-name() for disambiguation. Inputs are log files; output is logs to stdout.
