TITLE: Configuring Local and Network Logging - syslog-ng Config
DESCRIPTION: Extends the syslog-ng configuration to accept both local system logs and log messages from the network (listening on TCP port 514 by default). Maintains the same output destination file. Dependencies: 'scl.conf', syslog-ng with networking (network() source) enabled. Key parameters: system() and network() as sources; file() as destination. Input: local and remote syslog messages; Output: unified log file. Constraints: No filtering by source; all logs written to the same file.
SOURCE: https://github.com/syslog-ng/syslog-ng/blob/develop/README.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: config
CODE:
```
@version: current\n@include \"scl.conf\"\n\nlog {\n\tsource {\n\t\tsystem();\n\t\tnetwork();\n\t};\n\tdestination { file(\"/var/log/syslog\"); };\n};
```

